- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `nums` must have a length greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 10^4.
- Each element in the integer array parameter `nums` must be within the range of -100 to 100.
- The integer parameter `k` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 10^4.
- The integer result is the largest possible sum of the integer array `nums` after applying the process of choosing an index `i` and replacing `nums[i]` with `-nums[i]` exactly `k` times.